This paper deals with off-policy reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the method of off-policy corrections for reinforcement learning, which is a technique used in deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with computer vision (Atari games) and robotics (reinforcement learning), making cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also discusses the expected behavior of the off-policy learning algorithm, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with control systems (reinforcement learning), making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category.
